{
  "jacksonville": "In Jacksonville, specifically near Springfield Park, Atlantic storm bands can drive windthrow in mature Live Oaks and Slash Pines as saturated soils reduce root anchorage. Watch for root-plate heave and crown sail loading that creates lateral torsion at primary unions—common structural fail-points over sidewalks, homes, and nearby service drops. Our crews follow ANSI Z133 safety standards, establishing exclusion zones and performing hazard mitigation with high-angle rigging to lower compromised leaders and stabilize hangers. We document defect progression, loading vectors, and mitigation steps for loss mitigation packages supporting insurance claims.",
