  "tampa": "In Tampa at Riverside Park, Gulf storm bands can arrive with abrupt gust fronts that trigger windthrow in Live Oaks and Sand Pines when saturated soils weaken root cohesion. Sand Pines are prone to stem snap at structural fail-points, while Live Oaks may present root-plate heave and torsional shear at heavy scaffold unions. The immediate threat is impact to nearby homes, park structures, and utility corridors. Our crews operate to ANSI Z133 safety standards, deploying high-angle rigging to remove loaded hangers, reduce sail area, and stabilize hazards. We provide loss mitigation records aligned to insurance claim needs.",
  "orlando": "In Orlando near Lake Eola Park, inland-moving Atlantic bands can maintain strong gusts that exploit saturated soils around Live Oaks and Sabal Palms. Live Oaks often exhibit lateral torsion at extended limbs, leading to union failure and root-plate heave that can shift toward walkways and nearby structures. Palms may suffer crown attachment failures that become projectile hazards near roads and power lines. Following ANSI Z133 safety standards, our crews conduct hazard mitigation with high-angle rigging, controlled lowering, and stabilization cuts to isolate structural fail-points. We capture photos, measurements, and timelines for loss mitigation and insurance claims.",
  "st-petersburg": "In St. Petersburg, near Roser Park, coastal Atlantic storm bands can accelerate windthrow risks in Laurel Oaks and Live Oaks as saturated soils reduce holding strength and increase root-plate heave. Laurel Oaks commonly fail at structural fail-points in the upper canopy, while Live Oaks develop lateral torsion at heavy, horizontal limbs over streets and service lines. The immediate threat includes limb strikes to roofs, vehicles, and utility infrastructure. Our crews adhere to ANSI Z133 safety standards, using high-angle rigging to remove compromised leaders and stabilize remaining structure. We generate loss mitigation documentation to support insurance claim narratives.",
  "hialeah": "In Hialeah at Sparks Park, fast-moving Atlantic squalls can overload Royal Palms and Gumbo-Limbo, particularly when saturated soils undermine anchorage and conceal root-zone instability. Royal Palms may fail at crown connections, while Gumbo-Limbo can split at co-dominant stems—key structural fail-points under lateral torsion. The immediate hazard includes falling sections onto adjacent homes, pedestrian paths, and nearby utility runs. Under ANSI Z133 safety standards, our crews establish controlled work zones and apply high-angle rigging for precise lowering and hazard mitigation. We document damage mechanisms and stabilization steps for loss mitigation supporting insurance claims.",
  "port-st-lucie": "In Port St. Lucie near the North Fork River, Atlantic storm bands can combine gusting winds with saturated soils that elevate windthrow in Sabal Palms and Cypress. Cypress may lean as root plates shift, showing root-plate heave and compromised buttressing, while palms can fail at the crown or spear under dynamic loading. These hazards threaten river-adjacent structures, docks, and nearby utility lines. Our crews follow ANSI Z133 safety standards, using high-angle rigging to remove loaded tops and stabilize structural fail-points without collateral damage. We assemble loss mitigation documentation—photos, cut logs, and hazard notes—to support insurance claims.",
  "cape-coral": "In Cape Coral near Sun Splash Park, Gulf storm bands can deliver sustained gusts that trigger windthrow in Sabal Palms and Live Oaks, especially with saturated soils reducing root friction. Live Oaks can develop lateral torsion at heavy scaffolds, leading to sudden union failure and root-plate heave toward homes and roadways. Palms may suffer crown detachment that endangers park facilities and overhead utilities. Working to ANSI Z133 safety standards, our crews perform hazard mitigation using high-angle rigging for controlled lowering, canopy reduction, and stabilization of structural fail-points. We provide loss mitigation evidence packages for insurance claim support.",
