  "hollywood": "In Hollywood at Rotary Park, Gulf and Atlantic storm bands can generate short, violent gust cycles that destabilize Sabal Palms and Cypress, especially in saturated soils that reduce anchorage and increase root-zone movement. Cypress can shift with root-plate heave and lean progression, while palms may fail at the crown or spear, threatening nearby structures, park amenities, and utilities. Our crews follow ANSI Z133 safety standards, applying high-angle rigging to remove compromised tops and isolate structural fail-points through controlled dismantling and stabilization cuts. We provide loss mitigation documentation—photos, work logs, and hazard notes—for insurance claims.",
